sales columns: extra critic score: extra user score: extra

our measurements of success for a game have more values in the extra sales data, all sales may have more of other values but these are meaningless if we dont have a measurement for how successful the game is. Therefore extra_sales will be more useful.

GGally::ggcorr(extra_sales)
Warning: data in column(s) 'name', 'platform', 'year_of_release', 'genre', 'publisher', 'user_score', 'developer', 'rating' are not numeric and were ignored

the correlation between sales and critic score is weak, therefore we will keep both in as metrics of success instead of using just one.

all_sales %>% 
  filter(year > 2016 & is.na(global_sales) == FALSE)

The original data has games after 2016, but the new data doesnt. We can join these!
